# 1. Configuration Variables
@HostAddress = http://localhost:5217
# TIP: Replace this ID with one you get from the POST request below
@taskId = YOUR_PRODUCT_ID

### 1. Get All Tasks
# Use this to verify your MongoDB connection is working
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/tasks
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. Create a New Task
# This will insert a new document into your MongoDB Atlas collection
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Setup MongoDB Atlas",
  "description": "Connect the TaskManager microservice to the cloud database cluster.",
  "status": "In Progress"
}

###

### 3. Get Task by ID
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/tasks/{{taskId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. Update a Task (Put)
# This replaces the entire task document
PUT {{HostAddress}}/api/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "{{taskId}}",
  "title": "Setup MongoDB Atlas - COMPLETED",
  "description": "The connection is successful and tested.",
  "status": "Completed"
}

###

### 5. Delete a Task
DELETE {{HostAddress}}/api/tasks/{{taskId}}